Rating: 3
Variation: Sautee 1/3 cup minced shallots in 1 tbsp unsalted butter 3 minutes in a medium sauce pan. Add 3/4 cup merlot, 1 cup beef broth, 1 cup chicken broth, 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar. Simmer on med-high heat until mixture is reduced to 2/3 cup. Meanwhile, melt 1 tbsp. butter in large, heavy skillet. Salt and pepper 2 1.5 inch thick beef tenderloin steaks. Add to skillet, cook about 4 min. per side for med. rare. Put aside. Add the mixture from sauce pan to skillet, scrape any brown bits. Heat to simmer. Remove from heat, add 4 tbsp. unsalted butter to finish sauce. Spoon over steaks.

